<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a82fccf-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8116"><num value="8116">§ 8116.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a82fcd0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8116/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002584">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002584"><num>1</num> So in original. No subsec. (b) has been enacted.</note> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for each fiscal year such sums as may be necessary to carry out this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7a82fcd1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/110/403/tIII/s306">Pub. L. 110–403, title III, § 306</ref>, <date date="2008-10-13">Oct. 13, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/4270">122 Stat. 4270</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a82fcd2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a82fcd3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id7a82fcd4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This subchapter, referred to in subsec. (a), was in the original “this title”, meaning title III of <ref href="/us/pl/110/403">Pub. L. 110–403</ref>, <date date="2008-10-13">Oct. 13, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/4264">122 Stat. 4264</ref>, which is classified principally to this subchapter. For complete classification of title III to the Code, see Tables.</p>
</note>
</notes>
